  "prompt": "Indian Institutes of Technology (IITs): What is the fuss in IIT-M Periyar-Ambedkar study circle all about?",
  "response": "The controversy at IIT Madras involving the Periyar-Ambedkar Study Circle revolves around several key issues:\n\n1. Background:\n- The study circle is a student-led organization focused on discussing social issues\n- Named after social reformers Periyar E.V. Ramasamy and B.R. Ambedkar\n- Aims to promote social justice and discuss caste-related discrimination\n\n2. Initial Controversy:\n- The IIT Madras administration allegedly sought to derecognize the student group\n- Accused the study circle of creating \"hatred\" and disrupting campus harmony\n- Claimed their activities were against the institute's regulations\n\n3. Student Response:\n- Students viewed the move as an attack on freedom of expression\n- Argued that the study circle provides a platform for discussing critical social issues\n- Claimed the derecognition was an attempt to suppress dialogue on caste discrimination\n\n4. Public Reaction:\n- The incident drew significant media and public attention\n- Sparked debates about academic freedom and caste discrimination in educational institutions\n- Highlighted ongoing tensions regarding caste-related discussions in higher education\n\n5. Broader Context:\n- Reflects larger societal debates about caste, discrimination, and social justice\n- Raises questions about institutional responses to student activism\n\nThe controversy underscores complex dynamics of social discourse in Indian academic spaces.",
